"Steps:

 1.Click the switch button below to start capturing packets;

 2.Run the application that needs to be tested and access the network;

 3.Click the switch button below to stop capturing packets;

 4.Go to the log package and export the TcpDump log file;

 5.And then use the Wireshark tool to analyze the TcpDump log file
"

"Note: 1.To increase the node/cmd information, please turn off the log switch;
 2.When you add a node/cmd, check that you have not added in the node/cmd list.
 3.Before adding the node/cmd, please check whether there is permission to crawl log, if not add permission to their own."
